(96,	'The Divisibility Rule',	1,	'<p><strong style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The Divisibility Rule for</strong><span style=\"color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">&nbsp;5 is easily determined by&nbsp;checking the last digit in the given number. If the last number is either 0 or 5, then the entire number is divisible by 5. If the last digit in the number is 0, then the result will be the remaining digits multiplied by 2.</span><br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" /><a href=\"https://youtu.be/hz-hcXLK3y0\">https://youtu.be/hz-hcXLK3y0</a><br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" /><br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" /><strong style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The Divisibility Rule for 2&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">is used to&nbsp;determine&nbsp;if a&nbsp;number&nbsp;is&nbsp;divisible&nbsp;by&nbsp;2. You can also call it the test of&nbsp;divisibility&nbsp;for 2. A number is&nbsp;divisible&nbsp;by&nbsp;2&nbsp;if the last digit in the number is even. Even numbers are 0, 2, 4, 6, and 8.</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/xeMjYFUJC5k\">https://youtu.be/xeMjYFUJC5k</a><br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" /><br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\" /><strong style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">The divisibility rule of 3</strong><span style=\"color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">&nbsp;states that&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">if the sum of digits of a number is a multiple of 3, the number will be completely divisible by 3</strong><span style=\"color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #3c4043; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.2px;\"><a href=\"https://youtu.be/o9N9rmSaRSc\">https://youtu.be/o9N9rmSaRSc</a></span></p>',	'2022-11-29 11:09:11',	'2022-11-29 11:09:11',	NULL,	487,	1),
