(153,	'Global Citizenship Exam - vocabulary list',	6,	'<p><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif; color: black;\">The exam for global citizenship will be broken up into two parts. The first part will occur this Thursday, 8 December and cover the first chapter, Social Justice. The second part will occur next Monday, 12 December and cover the second chapter, Peace and Conflict.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; word-spacing: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif; color: black;\">The format of the test is primarily written. They will be asked to explain the concepts learned in each chapter. We will spend all of this week preparing for the exams, but it would also help to practice at home as the vocabulary may be a bit challenging.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; word-spacing: 0px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif; color: black;\">Here are the key vocabulary words for exam 1:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; word-spacing: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: \'Segoe UI\',sans-serif; color: black;\">injustice,&nbsp;bullying, poverty, support, relatively, inequality, society, perspective, opportunity, generalisation, harmful, stereotype, success</span></p>\r\n<p st