(232,	'Citizenship Exam- Monday 12th December',	6,	'<p>Dear parents,</p>\r\n<p>This is just a reminder that there is no Global Citizenship exam for Grade 3 tomorrow.&nbsp; Ours will be on <strong>Monday 12th December</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>As mentioned before, when looking through the Global Citizenship book, it will be useful for students to learn the vocabulary.&nbsp; They can either look in the glossary or in an online dictionary for revision.&nbsp; We have also been working a lot on learning the vocabulary this week in class.</p>\r\n<p>Here are some useful words from the book to learn:</p>\r\n<p><strong>assumption, opinion, stereotype, appearance, personality, wants, needs, live, thrive, essentials, barrier, equal, opportunity, activist, rights, protest, equality, inequality, judge, discrimination, prejudice, mistreat, justice, injustice, unjust, rights, thrive, wealth, poverty, gender, race, disability.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thank you,</p>\r\n<p>Miss Pam</p>',	'2022-12-07 13:04:00',	'2022-12-07 13:10:57',	NULL,	484,	1),
