(401,	'Fractions',	1,	'<p>Today we learned how to find parts of a fraction:<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>For Example</p>\r\n<p>1/2 of 10 = 5</p>\r\n<p>1/4 of 12 = 3</p>',	'2023-01-23 14:12:40',	'2023-01-23 14:12:40',	NULL,	483,	1),
(402,	'English',	3,	'<p>Today we began our unit in which we will learn how to write news stories.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We learned what a headline is.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We also differentiated headlines from headings which we learned about in our previous unit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-23 14:15:37',	'2023-01-23 14:15:37',	NULL,	483,	1),
(403,	'Science',	4,	'<p>Today we learned the difference among transparent, translucent and opaque.<br />We learned that the farther the sun is away the shorter a shadow will appear.&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-23 14:17:02',	'2023-01-23 14:17:02',	NULL,	483,	1),
(404,	'IPC - Chinese New Year - Year of the Rabbit - 2023',	5,	'<p>Dear All,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please practice the dance routine for the performance this week regarding Chinese New Year. To watch the video, please follow the link below.</p>\r\n<p><a style=\"color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://youtu.be/mrDltUY5x3Y\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://youtu.be/mrDltUY5x3Y&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1674471499947000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1aLXylu-KuSEJyNlLjlfBR\">https://youtu.be/mrDltUY5x3Y</a></p>\r\n<p>The celebration will be on <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Wednesday, January 25th, 2023 and Thursday, January 26th, 2023 during Lower and Upper Primary Assemblies.</span></p>\r\n<p>The costume will be as follows-</p>\r\n<p>Girls can dress up in red dresses and</p>\r\n<p>Boys may wear red shirt or t-shirt and black pants.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Love and Kind Regards,</p>\r\n<p>Ms. Viji</p>',	'2023-01-23 14:48:05',	'2023-01-23 14:48:05',	NULL,	476,	1),
(405,	'Homework - Speech Topic (Research)',	3,	'<p>Be sure to decide on a topic for your informative speech, research your topic, and record where you got the information.</p>\r\n<p>In the next class we will be drafting our speeches, so it is very important that you come to class with the information you need to write.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As a side note, I just wanted to say how awesome you guys were today with our improv activities!! I\'m really enjoying your stories.</p>',	'2023-01-23 15:11:22',	'2023-01-23 15:11:22',	NULL,	525,	1),
(406,	'Science Homework',	4,	'<p>Students need to classify the following animals.</p>\r\n<p>Camel, cat, ostrich, and sparrowhead</p>\r\n<p>I taught them how to classify in the classroom.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The first question is: Does it have four legs?</p>\r\n<p>Students will answer a yes or no answer.</p>\r\n<p>The students will ask another question, such as, does it have paws? If \"yes\", it is a cat. If \"no\" the animal is a camel.</p>\r\n<p>If this is too difficult for them, we will go over it in class tommorow.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you.</p>\r\n<p>Ms. Lilly</p>',	'2023-01-23 15:13:49',	'2023-01-23 15:13:49',	NULL,	524,	1),
(407,	'Homework - Speech (Research)',	3,	'<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Be sure to decide on a topic for your informative speech, research your topic, and record the information on your research source sheet.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">In the next class we will be drafting our speeches, so it is very important that you come to class with the information you need to write.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">I also wanted to say that your stories are look awesome! I am impressed by the creativity I am seeing from many of you!</p>',	'2023-01-23 15:16:30',	'2023-01-23 15:16:30',	NULL,	525,	1),
(408,	'Homework - Speech (Research)',	3,	'<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Be sure you have your topic for your informative speech. Complete your research on your topic and record where you got the information on your Research Source Sheet. We will be going over how to cite in MLA format.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">In the next class we will be drafting our speeches, so it is very important that you come to class with the information you need to write.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">I also wanted to say how much I appreciate your contributions to our improv activities today! Keep it up!!</p>',	'2023-01-23 15:21:53',	'2023-01-23 15:21:53',	NULL,	525,	1),
(409,	'Human Nutrition',	4,	'<p>Complete the Human Nutrition Workbook tonight. Pages 10-11 will be finished in class, as he started the experiment in the class room.&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-23 17:15:00',	'2023-01-23 17:15:00',	NULL,	520,	1),
(410,	'Optional No Red Ink: Capitalization lesson',	3,	'<p><a title=\"No Red Ink Capitalization \" href=\"https://www.noredink.com/learn/assignments/6492643\">Capitalization </a></p>\r\n<p>This is optional but many of the students will benifit from this.</p>',	'2023-01-23 17:19:48',	'2023-01-23 17:19:48',	NULL,	520,	1),
(411,	'Optional Prime Numbers',	1,	'<p>This is optional but will help the students. I assigned a Prime Number lesson in Khan Academy.</p>',	'2023-01-23 17:22:47',	'2023-01-23 17:22:47',	NULL,	520,	1),
(412,	'IPC',	5,	'<p>IPC homework: Worksheet: Animals in their habitat</p>\r\n<p>Worksheeet provided to students.</p>\r\n<p>They must complete and return on Wednesday.</p>',	'2023-01-24 07:25:54',	'2023-01-24 07:25:54',	NULL,	524,	1),
(413,	'angles and parallel lines',	1,	'<p>Hi, everybody!!!</p>\r\n<p>the homework will be on page 85 in the workbook!</p>\r\n<p>good luck!</p>\r\n<p>;)</p>',	'2023-01-24 09:54:10',	'2023-01-24 09:54:10',	NULL,	526,	1),
(414,	'Homework - Speech Draft',	3,	'<p>Today we spent a large portion of class making our speech outlines and starting to draft our speeches. Your homework for tonight is to finish writing your speech.</p>\r\n<p>In our next class, we will be completing peer edits and rehearsing. It is a good idea to say your speech aloud and time yourself to ensure you are within the 3-5 minute window.</p>',	'2023-01-24 14:17:46',	'2023-01-24 14:17:46',	NULL,	525,	1),
(415,	'Homework - Speech Draft',	3,	'<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">Today we spent a large portion of class making our speech outlines and starting to draft our speeches. Your homework for tonight is to finish writing your speech.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; margin: 0px; color: #76838f; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">In our next class, we will be completing peer edits and rehearsing. It is a good idea to say your speech aloud and time yourself to ensure you are within the 3-5 minute window.</p>',	'2023-01-24 14:19:26',	'2023-01-24 14:19:26',	NULL,	525,	1),
(416,	'English',	3,	'<p>Good Afternoon Parents</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The white story book went home today so they can read Animal Crackers - Camel and study these 4 word.</p>\r\n<p>camel, hump, raod, bumpy</p>\r\n<p>They will have a spelling test on Sunday and bring the books back on Sunday please.</p>\r\n<p>Thank You</p>\r\n<p>Ms Linda</p>',	'2023-01-24 15:13:29',	'2023-01-24 15:13:29',	NULL,	478,	1),
(417,	'Exam preparation',	3,	'<p>We will have an English exam on Monday 30th January. This English exam will be a reading comprehension exam, and we will practice reading comprehension in class this week.</p>\r\n<p>There will be questions about adverbs and pronouns, and the past tense.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will also have a Maths exam on the 29th January. The exam will cover addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, rounding, fractions and graphs.</p>\r\n<p>Good luck</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-24 15:26:15',	'2023-01-24 15:26:15',	NULL,	495,	1),
(418,	'IPC Homework - research',	5,	'<p>Each student should complete their research sheet about a country for IPC using the internet.</p>',	'2023-01-24 15:32:16',	'2023-01-24 15:32:16',	NULL,	495,	1),
(419,	'Homework - January',	6,	'<p>Please prepare for your science experiement tomorrow. Also, finish pages 84 and 85 in your Global Citizenship workbook by Sunday. Thank you.&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-24 15:37:02',	'2023-01-24 15:37:02',	NULL,	521,	1),
(420,	'IPC',	5,	'<p>Draw the original Baghdad. Today we learned about the history of Baghdad. The students began drawing the original planned city. As homework, they should finished drawing the city.</p>\r\n<p>We watched and discussed the following video in class. The students might want to look at it for help in their drawing.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"The History Of Baghdad: The Medieval World\'s Greatest City\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ovbkDxYWhpY\">The History Of Baghdad: The Medieval World\'s Greatest City</a></p>',	'2023-01-24 16:25:14',	'2023-01-24 16:25:14',	NULL,	520,	1),
(421,	'Homework - Complete Speech Outline, Citizenship Homework',	3,	'<p>Complete your speech outline. You should be prepared to come to class tomorrow with the basics of your speech so that we can do peer editing.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For citizenship, the back of your HDI paper should be complete by Sunday.</p>\r\n<p>For the backside, you are doing independent research about the countries whose Development Index you looked at in the computer lab. You can look at politics, infastructure, economics, etc. and describe some of the factors affecting the development of the country.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Example</span>: If you chose to look at Mali (whose mean years of schooling is 2.3 years) and Malaysia (whose mean years of schooling is 10.6 years), you would look into possible factors for why Mali\'s mean years of schooling is less than 3, while Malaysia\'s is almost 11.</p>\r\n<p>Questions you might investigate are: What are some reasons why people may not go to school? Are schools accessible or affordable? Is it safe to go to school? What are children doing if they are not in school? Who is responsible for managing schools?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You will do this for each of the dimensions of the Human Development Index.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When we return to class on Sunday, I will collect this paper and we will complete our investigation into The Universal Declaration of Human Rights.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-25 12:50:42',	'2023-01-25 12:50:42',	NULL,	525,	1),
(422,	'Homework - Speech',	3,	'<p>You should be prepared on Sunday to present your speech.</p>\r\n<p>Remember grading criteria:</p>\r\n<p>-3-5 minutes in length</p>\r\n<p>-Clear, organized content</p>\r\n<p>-Poise</p>\r\n<p>-Eye contact</p>\r\n<p>-Volume</p>',	'2023-01-25 12:53:09',	'2023-01-25 12:53:09',	NULL,	525,	1),
(423,	'Homework - Speech Outline',	3,	'<p>Come to class tomorrow with your speech outline completed so we can complete peer edits on Thursday.&nbsp;</p>',	'2023-01-25 12:54:19',	'2023-01-25 12:54:19',	NULL,	525,	1),
(424,	'Maths homework - Division',	1,	'<p>Textbook page 40 exercises 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6</p>',	'2023-01-25 14:15:00',	'2023-01-25 14:15:00',	NULL,	495,	1),
(425,	'English spelling revision',	3,	'<p>I have given each student a list of 100 common words in English. They will bring them home for spelling practice. It is essential that all students can spell these words correctly. We will have tests to check that students know how to spell all of these words.</p>',	'2023-01-25 14:19:01',	'2023-01-25 14:19:01',	NULL,	495,	1),
(426,	'Maths exam',	1,	'<p>The Maths exam on Sunday is the end of term exam for Term 1. It will be about everything we have covered so far in Maths. Look at Maths textbook 1.</p>',	'2023-01-26 12:38:48',	'2023-01-26 12:38:48',	NULL,	495,	1);
