(384,	'G8 Weekly Lesson Objectives 15/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\nInspire English International Student Book - Unit 3. Sections 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10. \r\nExploring structure - Understanding and linking key ideas; Summarising key ideas; Tricky terminology; Exploring structure; Responding to structure; Planning a description\r\nResponding to character - Identifying and inferring key details; Exploring the writer’s intention; Responding to vocabulary choice; Building a response paragraph; Writing a response. \r\nAssessment\r\nLooking at language choice - Gathering impressions; Building impressions through vocabulary choice; Identifying figurative language; Exploring language choice; Writing a response.\r\nRestructuring sentences - Responding to the text; Exploring sentence structure; Non-finite clauses; Experimenting with sentence structure; Writing a description\r\nDeveloping your response - Responding to key ideas; Exploring vocabulary choices; Using synonyms to refer back; Exploring structure; Exploring sentence structure; Planning a response\r\n\r\nMath\r\n*Understand types of prisms\r\n*Understand the formula to find the area of the base or area of cross section of the given prism\r\n*Calculate the volume of the given prism using the base area and length(height) of the prism\r\n*Calculate the unknown length or height of the base if volume of the prism is known.\r\n\r\nScience\r\n Know, draw and interpret pyramids of biomass.\r\n  Understand the terms ‘species’, ‘population’, ‘community’, ‘habitat’ and ‘ecosystem’.\r\n  Know the difference between inter- and intra-specific competition.\r\n  Know how to interpret data on population numbers.\r\n  Explain why population numbers fluctuate, including predator–prey relationships.\r\n  Know about predator–prey interactions in order to interpret data. \r\n\r\nIMYC\r\n Edward Bernays - His life and his work. How he used propaganda to make America into a more consumerist society. By the end students will be able to discuss the positive and negative impact of technology on the time period in which they were made. \r\n\r\nArabic\r\n درسنا الحال في هذا الاسبوع صفحة 74 الأسماء المجرورة صفحة 85 واخذنا المهارات القرائية صفحة 143 و 144 و 145 و 146 \r\n\r\nCitizenship\r\nPeaceful conflict resolution(peacebuilding & peacekeeping)\r\nPresentation on the history of the Cold War\r\n\r\nICT\r\nConsolidate nomenclature of waveforms in digitized audio formats (amplitude, pitch, frequency)\r\nFurther practice with audio editing software (Audacity)\r\nCalculating audio files sizes\r\nUnderstanding storage devices and storage media\r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards,\r\n EISB Management',	24,	'2023-01-15 12:25:22',	'2023-01-15 12:25:22',	NULL),
