(406,	'G8 weekly Lesson Objective 22/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\nInspire English International Student Book Unit 3. Sections 7, 8, 9, 10, 11\r\nLooking at Language choice - Gathering impressions; Building impressions through vocabulary choices; Identifying figurative language; Writing a response. \r\nRestructuring a sentence - Responding to the text; Exploring sentence structure; Non-finite clauses; Experimenting with sentence structure; Writing a description.\r\nDeveloping your response - Responding to key ideas; Exploring vocabulary choices; Using synonyms to refer back; Exploring structure; Exploring sentence structure; Planning your response\r\nMaking comparisons - Identifying key ideas; Comparing key ideas; Practising conjunction for comparison; Comparing how ideas are presented; Writing a comparison\r\nAssessment\r\n\r\nMath\r\nCalculate the circumference of a circle\r\nSolve problems involving circles or prisms\r\nIdentify the circumference,arc and sector of a circle\r\nSolve problems involving circles,semicircles and different combinations including polygons.\r\n\r\nScience\r\nKnow the role of decomposers in recycling carbon in an ecosystem. \r\n Know examples of production of carbon dioxide by human activity and discuss the impact of these on the climate.\r\nKnow the structure of an atom in terms of the positions of sub-atomic particles.\r\n Know the relative charges of protons, neutrons and electrons.\r\n  Understand and use the terms ‘atomic (proton) number’ and ‘mass number’.\r\n\r\nIMYC\r\n The United Nations - how it works\r\n\r\nArabic\r\nالمفاعيل الخمسة ( المفعول به صفحة 63 والمفعول المطلق صفحة 65 والمفعول لأجله صفحة 66 ) بالإضافة إلى المهارات القرائية \r\n\r\nCitizenship\r\nPresentations on the Cold War\r\nOverview and research on current UN peacekeeping operations\r\n\r\nICT\r\nCalculate audio file sizes for a range of scenarios\r\nUnderstand the purpose and differences between storage devices and storage media\r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards,\r\n EISB Management',	24,	'2023-01-22 13:41:08',	'2023-01-22 13:41:08',	NULL),
(407,	'G9 Weekly Lesson Objectives 22/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\n *Be sure you are coming to class each day with a notebook\r\n\r\nAssessment Objectives - Exam Connection: \r\n3A Understand the overall message of a spoken passage\r\n3B Identify essential and finer points of detail in spoken material\r\n3D Identify a speaker\'s viewpoint and attitude, stated and implied\r\n4A Give information on a range of topics at different levels of complexity\r\n4B Respond to a range of questions\r\n\r\nUnit Focus: Speech and Debate\r\n-Students will be able to identify key features (in both structure and delivery) of an effective informative speech. Structural focus on developing a hook, supporting details, closing statements, and adapting speeches to a target audience.\r\n-Students will conduct research, draft, and workshop informative speeches on topics of their choice. \r\nSupport Activities: Group improv exercises, analyzing examples of public speaking\r\nGrammar and Writing: Question Tags (The weather is quite nice today, isn\'t it?), MLA citations, identifying and using credible sources\r\n\r\nMath\r\n Use set notation\r\nUse venn diagrams to represent sets\r\n\r\nScience\r\n The Periodic Table and Chemical Formula/Equations. Chemistry Chapters 4 and 5.\r\n\r\nBusiness\r\n Review chapters 1 and 2 - core concepts, vocabulary\r\nTeach: chapter 3 pages 19 - 26\r\nWhat is a partnership? Pros and cons (review from last week)\r\nSocial enterprises - why do they exist, who do they help; organizational structure; who are the stakeholders\r\nFranchises - how are they organized; pros and cons\r\n\r\nCitizenship\r\nMeasuring development (HDI) Webquest\r\nExamining the articles of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights\r\n\r\nArabic \r\nاخذنا موضوع الأسماء الخمسة  صفحة 78 وقمنا بحل التمرينات وموضوع التمييز صفحة 80 و الأسماء المجرورة صفحة 85 \r\n\r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards,\r\n EISB Management',	25,	'2023-01-22 13:43:31',	'2023-01-22 13:43:31',	NULL),
(408,	'G1 Weekly Lesson Objectives 22/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\nStory: \r\nAnimal Crackers and Brave Little Beasts\r\nLearn to say a rhyming poem out loud.\r\nHow to add actions and use your face to make a performance more interesting.\r\nHow to work in a team to perform a poem.\r\nTricky words\r\nPunctuation - example, punctuation can show us where a sentence begins and ends.\r\nHow to use an exclamation mark.\r\n\r\n \r\nMath\r\nHow to add 2 digit numbers\r\nTens and ones add and subtract\r\nHow to do Place-value additions and subtraction\r\nAdding and subtracting 10 and 11\r\nHow to adding 9\r\nCounting back in 10s\r\n\r\nScience\r\nHabitats: \r\nExtreme Habitats.\r\nMicro-habitats\r\nContrasting Habitats.\r\nMinibeasts.\r\n\r\nIPC\r\nExplore different holidays and celebrations.\r\nIntroduction into basic vocabulary related to holidays and celebrations.\r\n\r\nArabic\r\nدراسة حرف م والتدرب على م مع حروف (ا-و-ي) والحركات القصيرة (فتحة-ضمة-كسرة-سكون) اضافة إلى التدريبات الصوتية الخاصة بالحرف ص 62\r\nتدريبات ص61 إلى ص 72\r\nقراءة ص66\r\n\r\nArt\r\n Learn how to do draw James Rizzi birds\r\n\r\nCitizenship\r\nUnderstand how to recognize a mistake.\r\nLearn the importance of telling the truth.\r\nLearn how to admit mistakes and apologize.\r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards, \r\n EISB Management',	17,	'2023-01-22 14:29:00',	'2023-01-22 14:44:06',	NULL),
