(416,	'G7 Weekly Lesson Objective 22/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\nReview vocabulary words and definitions.\r\nThis Thursday definitions quiz on same vocabulary words pgs 84, 98, 106\r\nReading an argumentative extract pg 98\r\nDiscussing and planning their own argumentative writing\r\nIdentify and understand a topic sentence for each paragraph\r\nGrammar- subject/verb agreement\r\nHomework- grammar paper given in class\r\nReading comprehension- current events\r\nWriting- writing an argumentative paper, what isnt completed in class is homework.\r\nAlso remember 30 minutes a day reading something they enjoy.\r\n\r\nMath\r\n -Calculate the interior and exterior angles of an\r\nirregular or regular polygon.\r\n -Solve geometric problems using side and angle\r\nproperties of quadrilaterals and other polygons.\r\n\r\nScience\r\nKnow Dalton’s atomic model.\r\n  Know common chemical symbols and common chemical formulae.\r\n Know common formulae, including salt (NaCl) and limestone (CaCO3 ).\r\n Understand that chemical formulae show the ratio of elements in a compound and be able to use these formulae.\r\nDescribe the combustion of elements in oxygen\r\n Understanding the term ‘oxidation’ is the gain of oxygen.\r\n\r\nIMYC\r\n Geography project using Google maps\r\nGeography project using the internet planning for a holiday\r\nCreating a Venn diagram based on classroom made maps\r\n\r\nArabic\r\nإعراب الضمائر المتصلة والمنفصلة والمستترة مع حفظ موضوع طه حسين\r\n\r\nCitizenship\r\nConflicts n disputes\r\nResolving conflicts\r\nBook pgs 64-70\r\nAlso make up pages from my absences last week.\r\n\r\nICT\r\nUnderstand the requirements of a simple file transfer calculator\r\nCreate a visual-coding calculator\r\nCreate a Python based bandwidth calculator\r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards,\r\n EISB Management',	23,	'2023-01-23 10:0