(418,	'G10 Weekly Lesson Objectives 22/1/2023',	'Dear Parent,\r\nYour child will be studying the following material this week:\r\n\r\nEnglish\r\n*Be sure you are coming to class each day with a notebook\r\n\r\nAssessment Objectives - Exam Connection: \r\n3A Understand the overall message of a spoken passage\r\n3B Identify essential and finer points of detail in spoken material\r\n3D Identify a speaker\'s viewpoint and attitude, stated and implied\r\n4A Give information on a range of topics at different levels of complexity\r\n4B Respond to a range of questions\r\n\r\nUnit Focus: Speech and Debate\r\n-Students will be able to identify key features (in both structure and delivery) of an effective informative speech. Structural focus on developing a hook, supporting details, closing statements, and adapting speeches to a target audience.\r\n-Students will conduct research, draft, and workshop informative speeches on topics of their choice. \r\nSupport Activities: Group improv exercises, analyzing examples of public speaking\r\nGrammar and Writing: Question Tags (The weather is quite nice today, isn\'t it?), MLA citations\r\n\r\nMath\r\n Use Venn diagram to represent sets\r\nUse set builder notations\r\n\r\nScience\r\n The Electromagnetic Spectrum and Light/Sound Waves. Physics chapters 8 and 9.\r\n\r\nBusiness\r\n 10A: technology in production\r\nQuiz based on book pp364-365; finish chapter 43, read & analyze text p367\r\n\r\nGeography \r\n10B: Review - destructive waves vs constructive waves; how are they formed, differences in the processes of each;\r\nStudy book pages up to 39 (homework: read and take notes - annotations on unknown words)\r\nLandforms - creative processes and landforms made by destructive processes (beaches, river deltas VS  bays and headlands, cliff, arch, stack)\r\nWeathering erosion and mass movement; hydraulic action abrasion and corrosion; \r\nWorksheet 4 (in class)\r\n 10A: urbanization - increase in population (drawing) the processes the reasons the results\r\nThree stages of urbanization: slow increase - rapid increase - decline - ???future\r\nincrease in area: urban sprawl; suburbanize \r\n\r\nArabic \r\n اخذنا المجرورات صفحة 85 والاسم الممنوع من الصرف صفحة 89 \r\n\r\n If you require any further clarification please feel free to reach out to our school.\r\n\r\n Regards,\r\n EISB Management',	26,	'2023-01-23 10:12:25',	'2023-01-23 10:12:25',	NULL),
